Sentencas: Here, we report a cobalt spinel oxide (Co3O4) and gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) nano -composite cathode to achieve superior performance and durability in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A simple sol-gel process was used to create the Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite, which allowed for separate precipitation of the Co3O4 and GDC phases during calcination.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: HR-TEM revealed the nanocrystalline nature of the composite, consisting of nanocrystallites ranging in size from 5 to 10 nm.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD and HAADF-STEM showed the formation of two distinct phases.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SOFC, consisting of a Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode, showed high durability while operating at 800 degrees C for 300 h under a galvanostatic load of 1 A cm-2.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SOFC exhibited a continuously increasing performance, achieving a maximum power density of 1382 mW cm-2 after a 300 h operation.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The findings demonstrate the efficacy of using Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for superior electrochemical performance as well as durability for the advancement of SOFC technology.
Titulo: A highly stable Co3O4-GDC nanocomposite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
